description.narrative: By October 2019, the policy on Focused Antenatal Care had been developed and adapted and is currently being implemented nationwide. Some 90% of pregnant women had received IPT2, far exceeding the annual target of 60%. Institutional deliveries also increased from the 2018 baseline value of 51% to 53%, while births attended by a skilled attendant also improved from 50% in 2018 to 52% in October 2019. | Status:Met | As-of Date:16/01/2020
